<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Search for Objects Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Search for Objects Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Search for Objects</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is used to select objects based on which data sets they affect.  To display the dialog box, select </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Object|Search for Objects...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">  Next the user checks the checkboxes next to the data sets and clicks the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">OK</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button.  If any objects set that data set directly by specifying a formula for it, they will be selected.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">See also: </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Selected_Objects_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Selected Objects</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box and </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Show_or_Hide_Objects_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Show or Hide Objects</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
